				<description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;cherry---mimic-ctf-finals-2025&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Cherry - Mimic CTF Finals 2025&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#cherry---mimic-ctf-finals-2025&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Two weeks ago I went to Nanjing, China to take part in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://ctftime.org/event/2999&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;2025 Qiangwang Challenge on Cyber Mimic Defense Finals&lt;/a&gt; with the ARESx team. Me and &lt;a href=&#34;[https://leo1.cc/]%28https://leo1.cc/&#34; title=&#34;https://leo1.cc/&#34; &gt;@leo_something&lt;/a&gt;) full cleared pwn during the CTF and in this writeup we are going to talk about a really nice browser challenge we encountered.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Overview&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#overview&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The challenge consisted in a patched version of &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/jerryscript-project/jerryscript&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;jerryscript&lt;/a&gt;, a &amp;ldquo;lightweight JavaScript engine intended to run on a very constrained devices such as microcontrollers&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
